<ul><li>Search the <a title="Find Library Materials" href="services-programs/outlook-online-help/finding-library-materials.html">Library Catalogue</a></li></ul>
<ul><li><a title="Feedback Form" href="contacts/feedback-form.html">Library Contacts</a><br /><br /></li></ul>
<h2>What's New</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2><strong>Do you have gift cards you don't need ?<br /></strong></h2>
<p>If you have gift cards you don't need, please consider donating them to the . Cards with proof of value will be given a <strong>charitable donation receipt</strong> for 90% of the value and our heartfelt thanks for helping the library remain open.</p>
<p>______________________________________________</p>
<h2><strong>View Royal Reading Centre 70th<br /></strong></h2>
<p>In 2013 View Royal Reading Centre celebrated <strong>70 years</strong> of providing library service to View Royal residents. A commemorative mug is available for $10 at the library. Proceeds will go to funding the library, so that we may remain open.</p>
<p>_________________________________________</p>
<h3>Volunteers needed</h3>
<p>If you would like to help keep the library running please contact us at the library, by email or call 250-479-2723.</p>
<p>______________________________________________</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2><strong>View Royal Reading Centre gets its happy ending - for now</strong></h2>
<div style="text-align: center;" class="media">
               
                    <img title="GNG-readingcentre2Poct1712.jpg" src="images/96600goldstreamGNG-readingcentre2Poct1712.jpg" alt="GNG-readingcentre2Poct1712.jpg" height="302" width="460" border="0" />
                                <br />
<div style="text-align: left;" class="byline">
                Doreen Jackman, director of the View Royal Reading 
Centre, is delighted the centre will remain open at its current location
 for at least another year to serve the community.</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class="byline">				
							
 		
							
								
		

		 
             

			

				


By <a href="http://www.goldstreamgazette.com/about_us/">Kyle Wells - Goldstream News Gazette</a><br />
			
							
				Published: <strong>October 19, 2012 12:00 PM</strong></div>
<p>At the 11th hour the View Royal Reading Centre is
 saved from closing and will remain at its current location for at least
 another year.</p>
<p>It was down to the wire for the local libraryâs 
organizers, who were looking into other options as an Oct. 31 deadline 
to come up with either more funding or a new home loomed. Now, thanks to
 the help of some local politicians and a willing landlord, the rent 
will be reduced for the centre.</p>
<p>âRelief,â said library manager Doreen Jackman of 
her reaction to the news. ââOh thank God, weâve got it resolved.â Itâs 
just been a stress on the whole committee.â</p>
<p>The centre, which will celebrate its 70th 
anniversary next year, survives on donations, sales of books no longer 
needed, money raised from bake sales and other events and an annual 
$25,000 grant from the Town of View Royal. The centre used to receive 
money from the province until all funding for reading centres was cut 
about two years ago.</p>
<p>Earlier in the year the committee that runs the 
centre determined it would not be able to afford to keep the 
long-running institution going. The date for closure was set for the end
 of the month, unless a new source of funding or a new location could be
 found.</p>
<p>âWe were quite sure there was no further funding 
coming,â Jackman said. âNobody was interested in having us and we 
couldnât afford to move anywhere. It was âoh, I guess weâll have to 
close.ââ</p>
<p>With the help of View Royal Mayor Graham Hill and
 Coun. David Screech, reading centre staff talked to the managers and 
owner of the Admirals Walk plaza, who agreed to charge the centre a 
cheaper rate so they can afford to stay on.</p>
<p>âItâs a pretty amazing deal really, for that 
space,â Screech said. âI certainly respect what they do there, I think 
all of council does. We value their work and what they offer.â</p>
<p>The agreement is only for one year, at which point the centre will have to reopen talks about staying in the location.</p>
<p>âItâs a great relief to all of us that weâre 
going to be staying here,â Jackman said. âWe like all the people that 
come in and out. Most of them we know by name.â</p>
<p>The centre moved from the old View Royal town 
hall to its current location four years ago. Since then Jackman said the
 centre has thrived, with about 1,200 patrons signed up and a 
circulation of 600 to 800 books per month.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Volunteers are always needed, as are donations. For more information call 250-479-2723 or email</p>
<p>vivr.ill@shaw.ca.</p>
<h3><a class="external-link" href="services-programs/collections.html">2014 UP-DATE</a></h3>
<p>We have been very fortunate in receiving book donations from many of our members, this has been one way that we are able to save a considerable amount of money; books are our major expense.&nbsp; With these donations we have been able to replenish the shelves and replace any books that are looking a little tattered; we have been putting these on the sale rack, and this has helped our finances.</p>
<p>The "<strong>Smile Card</strong>" program, through <strong>Thrifty Foods</strong>, is an on-going success, a great way to help your food budget, and a wonderful way to help the library.&nbsp; We have been very fortunate to receive some corporate donations again this year, as well as from individual members.&nbsp; <strong>THANK YOU!!!</strong></p>
<p>We have noticed that there has been a big demand for DVDs, so we have been able to purchase a large quantity of them at reduced prices.&nbsp; These are suitable for all ages.&nbsp; The borrowing period is for one week, and we are allowing for three DVDs to be taken at any one time.&nbsp; The children's department now has a new, large selection of Walt Disney DVDs, (all up-to-date titles).</p>
<p>Just to let you know, we have almost 1,200 patrons, many being loyal members for many years, and a large number of new patrons - welcome - it is really great to realize that you are all supporters of <strong><u>your library</u>!</strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Website: <a class="external-link" href=".html">http://viewroyal.bclibrary.ca</a></p>
<p>Email: <a class="external-link" href="mailto:vivr.ill@shaw.ca">vivr.ill@shaw.ca</a></p>

